## TanStack Form 1.27 Rules
```tsx
// Correct form setup
const form = useForm({
  defaultValues: { username: '', password: '' },
  validators: { onChange: schema as any }, // `as any` is intentional — Zod v4 workaround
  onSubmit: async ({ value }) => { onSubmit(value); },
});

// Correct field rendering
<form.Field name="username" children={field => (
  <Input value={field.state.value} onChangeText={field.handleChange} />
)} />

// Correct submit button
<form.Subscribe selector={state => state.isSubmitting} children={isSubmitting => (
  <Button onPress={form.handleSubmit} loading={isSubmitting} />
)} />
```

- Do NOT bypass `form.handleSubmit` — it runs Zod validation before calling `onSubmit`
- Do NOT remove the `as any` cast — it is the accepted workaround for Zod v4 + TanStack Form v1.27 TypeScript compatibility
- Do NOT introduce `react-hook-form` anywhere in this codebase

